            "answer_text": "The ratio of the age of A & B is 7:9. After 3 years, the ratio becomes 4:5. What are their ages? Solution: At present A is 7x and B is 9x years old. In 3 years from now, (7x+3):(9x+3) = 4:5, or 35x+15 = 36x+12, or x = 3 So A is 21 years now, and B is 27 years. Answer. ",
